    <h3>The Six Elements of Professional Relationships</h3>
    <p>Six “elements” (Insights, Onboarding, Engagement, Communication, Appreciation and Recognition, and Disruptions) are the main categories that make up all professional relationships because while the tactics may change, the main buckets remain consistent. And when companies can compartmentalize critical elements, it makes X both accessible and actionable. </p>
